  "contentFields": [
    {
      "contentFieldValue": {
        "data": "<p><span style=\"-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;\">Release Date: <a href=\"https://support.liferay.com/06-15-2023-release-updates\" target=\"_self\">06/15/2023</a></span></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>We're making a small, but handy update to our services. We've heard your feedback regarding the management of large log files, especially for those using custom services like Splunk.</p>\n<p>So, what's new?</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<strong>Log Rotation</strong>: From now on, Nginx service will handle log rotation automatically, removing the need for manual intervention.</li>\n<li>\n<strong>File Size Limit</strong>: Rotation will trigger once a log file hits a certain size. You can set this limit yourself, or use the default value we provide.</li>\n<li>\n<strong>File Naming</strong>: Post rotation, new files will end in '.0', with older files following a sequential order ('.1', '.2', etc.).</li>\n<li>\n<strong>Stability</strong>: The Nginx process will not be interrupted during rotation, ensuring your services continue running smoothly.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>We've tested this update extensively to ensure it works as expected. Any failure in the log rotation process will be handled and reported appropriately.</p>\n<p>We hope this update makes managing your logs just a bit easier.</p>"
      },
